  "texts": [
    "Evolution of the macroscopic quantities.",
    "In this subsection we are interested in studying the behavior of the macroscopic quantities ( 6)- (10) of the solution to the Fokker-Planck equation (13).",
    "In fact, this simplified formulation of the Boltzmann description (11) will allow us to derive explicit information regarding their evolution.Let us start by considering only the interactions agent-agent, namely A, w).",
    "The no-flux boundary conditions and the symmetry of the function G ensure the conservation of mass and of the average opinion m w, already obtained through the integro-differential equations (11) and (12).",
    "In particular, the evolution of the average opinion reads∂ t f (t, A, w) = Q p (f, f)(t,d dt m w (t) = -λ p ∫ R×I ( Āω p + ε)K[f](t, w)f (t, A, w)dAdw = -λ p ∫ R 2 ×I 2 ( Āω p + ε)( Bω p + ε)G(w, z)(w -z)f (t, A, w)f (t, B, z)dAdBdwdz = 0,from which we can see that, as expected, the opinion of the active agents varies faster than the opinion of the inactive ones."
  ]
